WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.800 --> 00:00:06.037
Praised be Jesus and Mary,
I warmly greet you all.

00:00:06.037 --> 00:00:11.545
I am glad you came this evening
to the Basilica of St. Anthony.

00:00:11.545 --> 00:00:15.358
To these spiritually-humorous
evenings, and before I start with

00:00:15.358 --> 00:00:21.714
the catechesis, I will tell you later
what the title is, but maybe you saw

00:00:21.714 --> 00:00:28.070
on social media, in the Sacristy we
have a box where we put lost items.

00:00:29.849 --> 00:00:34.932
So, we've accumulated a lot of
things that people, as we like

00:00:34.932 --> 00:00:37.474
to say, have scattered or lost.

00:00:37.474 --> 00:00:42.980
There are some items that I believe
some of you might have lost,

00:00:42.980 --> 00:00:47.640
maybe since last Thursday, so
let's see if anyone comes forward.

00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:51.452
To start, let's see
what we pull out first.

00:00:51.452 --> 00:00:53.570
Someone has lost their keys.

00:00:56.129 --> 00:00:58.489
Has anyone lost their keys?

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:04.834
Have you checked your pockets,
does everyone have their house

00:01:04.834 --> 00:01:07.519
keys so you can return home?

00:01:07.519 --> 00:01:13.783
If no one has lost their keys, maybe
you've lost what the keys represent.

00:01:13.783 --> 00:01:15.573
Maybe you've lost security.

00:01:15.573 --> 00:01:20.495
You know, to lock yourself
somewhere where no one can reach

00:01:20.495 --> 00:01:22.733
you, where you'll feel safe.

00:01:22.733 --> 00:01:28.550
Where no one can attack you, no
one can take something from you.

00:01:29.390 --> 00:01:33.863
But you might have also lost
many opportunities in your life.

00:01:33.863 --> 00:01:35.490
Or you squandered them.

00:01:35.490 --> 00:01:37.523
So now they are lost.

00:01:37.523 --> 00:01:43.216
Because each of these keys represents a
new door you could have walked through.

00:01:43.216 --> 00:01:47.690
Maybe you lost that if you
haven't already lost these keys.

00:01:53.455 --> 00:01:58.624
Someone also left a planner,
unfortunately, it doesn't

00:01:58.624 --> 00:02:01.855
have a name inside, but

00:02:05.215 --> 00:02:10.758
the planner is filled out
so you don't think it's not.

00:02:10.758 --> 00:02:13.277
So, someone lost a planner.

00:02:13.277 --> 00:02:17.309
Has any of you ever lost a planner?

00:02:17.309 --> 00:02:21.844
You see, maybe you've lost
what this planner represents.

00:02:21.844 --> 00:02:26.380
This planner represents meaning,
it represents life, the most

00:02:26.380 --> 00:02:31.923
vital meaning that you might
have lost and no longer have.

00:02:31.923 --> 00:02:35.955
Somewhere you misplaced
it, somewhere it got lost.

00:02:38.275 --> 00:02:43.761
Maybe some of you have lost
a cross, because what the

00:02:43.761 --> 00:02:46.255
cross represents is our faith.

00:02:49.975 --> 00:02:54.074
We can't say that we always
have enough faith in our lives.

00:02:54.074 --> 00:02:58.857
Maybe some of you have stopped believing,
maybe someone came here for the first

00:02:58.857 --> 00:03:03.981
time this Thursday to see what it's all
about, and maybe their faith will awaken,

00:03:03.981 --> 00:03:06.715
maybe you've lost that faith in your life.

00:03:09.545 --> 00:03:11.363
Someone lost their headphones.

00:03:11.363 --> 00:03:16.817
Obviously, when they came here to
the basilica, they heard God, so

00:03:16.817 --> 00:03:19.545
they no longer needed the headphones.

00:03:23.475 --> 00:03:27.708
Or maybe one of you has lost
what the headphones represent.

00:03:27.708 --> 00:03:31.942
Maybe you've lost your hearing
and can no longer hear God.

00:03:31.942 --> 00:03:35.790
Maybe you've lost communication
with Him and no longer understand

00:03:35.790 --> 00:03:37.715
what He's saying to you.

00:03:43.005 --> 00:03:44.785
Someone lost their ID card too.

00:03:47.640 --> 00:03:48.550
Filip Pintarić.

00:03:48.550 --> 00:03:52.649
Let's give a round of
applause for our Filip.

00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:53.560
Thank you.

00:03:58.519 --> 00:03:59.967
You are beautiful.

00:03:59.967 --> 00:04:04.792
He didn't lose his ID, I took it from him.

00:04:04.792 --> 00:04:07.687
Because this ID represents our identity.

00:04:07.687 --> 00:04:09.135
Who am I?

00:04:09.135 --> 00:04:13.959
And maybe some of you have
just lost your identity.

00:04:18.045 --> 00:04:24.548
Your identity, the fact that you
are a human being, a child of God,

00:04:24.548 --> 00:04:30.587
a beloved child of God, a believer,
a Christian, any kind of identity.

00:04:30.587 --> 00:04:36.161
All these lost things, somehow
when I talk about what is lost,

00:04:36.161 --> 00:04:38.484
always point us to someone.

00:04:38.484 --> 00:04:44.523
And that someone, considering we are
now in his basilica, is Saint Anthony.

00:04:44.523 --> 00:04:51.026
I believe that many times in your
life you have heard, if you haven't

00:04:51.026 --> 00:04:52.885
already experienced it yourself.

00:04:54.565 --> 00:05:02.051
If you lose something, they say, pray
to Saint Anthony and you will find it.

00:05:02.051 --> 00:05:08.040
This usually gets resolved very
quickly when we pray to Saint Anthony.

00:05:08.040 --> 00:05:14.029
And then we say, when we find
something we thought was lost

00:05:14.029 --> 00:05:17.024
forever, we call it a miracle.

00:05:17.024 --> 00:05:23.013
And today's topic that I will
talk to you about is precisely

00:05:23.013 --> 00:05:25.010
Saint Anthony and miracles.

00:05:27.719 --> 00:05:33.243
Imagine this now, as Stjepan first
told the participants, close your eyes.

00:05:33.243 --> 00:05:38.307
Get comfortable, you don't have to,
but imagine this: tomorrow morning

00:05:38.307 --> 00:05:45.211
when you wake up, you open your eyes
and then suddenly it hits you, that

00:05:45.211 --> 00:05:50.735
thing you've been praying for a long
time, something you've been searching

00:05:50.735 --> 00:05:57.179
for, something that was a deep desire
of your heart, it has come true.

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:05.902
What we thought was impossible to
achieve in our lives has just happened.

00:06:05.902 --> 00:06:12.085
You don't know how, you don't
know why, but you know it's real.

00:06:12.085 --> 00:06:16.365
Maybe it's reconciliation with
someone, coming out of darkness,

00:06:16.365 --> 00:06:21.596
maybe physical healing, maybe a
sense of peace you couldn't find.

00:06:21.596 --> 00:06:28.255
Maybe it's just the answer to that
question you couldn't find an answer to.

00:06:28.895 --> 00:06:36.560
But literally for any of these things to
happen, you can say a miracle occurred.

00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:42.182
And now, I ask each of you
individually, what would be

00:06:42.182 --> 00:06:45.248
a real miracle for you today?

00:06:45.248 --> 00:06:51.892
And perhaps an even more important
question than what would be a real

00:06:51.892 --> 00:06:58.024
miracle for you is, would you be
able to recognize that miracle?

00:06:58.024 --> 00:07:03.135
Would you be able to recognize
the miracle that happened?

00:07:05.735 --> 00:07:12.902
Maybe when you move in with someone,
can you recognize that as a miracle?

00:07:12.902 --> 00:07:20.070
Passing an exam you were sure you
would fail when you face the professor.

00:07:20.070 --> 00:07:25.189
When that anxiety you hide so
skillfully and deftly disappears,

00:07:25.189 --> 00:07:27.749
and you finally feel loved.

00:07:27.749 --> 00:07:34.917
Do you recognize, dear young people,
not just the young ones here but all

00:07:34.917 --> 00:07:42.085
of you, do you recognize the moments in
your life that are actually miracles?

00:07:44.479 --> 00:07:52.263
Miracles happen, I stand here today
before you and I have been given the

00:07:52.263 --> 00:08:00.604
task to tell you, yes you who are here
today, that God still performs miracles,

00:08:00.604 --> 00:08:03.940
we just often don't recognize them.

00:08:07.180 --> 00:08:08.641
Miracle, miracle, miracle.

00:08:08.641 --> 00:08:14.975
Miracle, miraculous, you have to
think, as one song in a musical says.

00:08:14.975 --> 00:08:21.310
When we say the word miracle, we
often think of something grand and

00:08:21.310 --> 00:08:26.669
extraordinary, something like from a
movie, from Hollywood, or maybe more

00:08:26.669 --> 00:08:32.516
from Bollywood—they have bigger miracles
there, like the sea parting, the blind

00:08:32.516 --> 00:08:35.440
seeing, or someone starting to fly.

00:08:37.930 --> 00:08:42.850
But all of that, we can say, is
something extraordinary, something we

00:08:42.850 --> 00:08:48.181
can't physically comprehend happening
before us, so we can call it a miracle.

00:08:48.181 --> 00:08:53.922
But we also need to be aware
that a miracle is not a trick

00:08:53.922 --> 00:08:56.793
and a miracle is not a circus.

00:08:56.793 --> 00:09:01.713
Because we've all seen magicians and
their tricks, and we see something

00:09:01.713 --> 00:09:06.224
flying if we don't know how it's
flying, or something disappearing

00:09:06.224 --> 00:09:09.095
if we don't know how it disappeared.

00:09:09.495 --> 00:09:14.862
But those are tricks, that's a
circus, that's entertainment,

00:09:14.862 --> 00:09:17.844
that's not a real miracle.

00:09:17.844 --> 00:09:21.423
So, what is a miracle then?

00:09:21.423 --> 00:09:26.194
A miracle is when God breaks the silence.

00:09:26.194 --> 00:09:29.773
When heaven intervenes in our reality.

00:09:29.773 --> 00:09:38.719
A miracle is, I repeat once more, the
moment when God touches our reality and

00:09:38.719 --> 00:09:48.858
through that says to us, "I am here,
do you see me?" And that is a miracle.

00:09:48.858 --> 00:09:56.015
The Church defines a miracle as an
event that transcends the natural

00:09:56.015 --> 00:10:00.190
laws, all those laws that we know.

00:10:00.190 --> 00:10:06.602
And that miracle, that phenomenon,
cannot be explained by any examinations,

00:10:06.602 --> 00:10:10.100
whether by medicine, science, or logic.

00:10:10.100 --> 00:10:17.096
It means something that we cannot explain
by any means, something extraordinary,

00:10:17.096 --> 00:10:23.509
without clear foundations that we
can document—that is truly a miracle.

00:10:23.509 --> 00:10:30.505
And when the church declares
miracles, it does not do so lightly.

00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:34.502
Something happened
there, that's a miracle.

00:10:34.502 --> 00:10:38.583
The Church will never say that lightly.

00:10:38.583 --> 00:10:43.246
Every miraculous occurrence is
thoroughly investigated by the

00:10:43.246 --> 00:10:49.659
Church, especially because for someone
to be declared a saint, certain

00:10:49.659 --> 00:10:51.990
miracles must occur beforehand.

00:10:51.990 --> 00:10:57.820
These extraordinary acts, attributed
to the intercession of that person,

00:10:57.820 --> 00:11:00.735
are necessary for their canonization.

00:11:02.005 --> 00:11:07.568
And every miracle, every phenomenon
undergoes very serious and strict

00:11:07.568 --> 00:11:12.575
examinations, both from a scientific
and a spiritual perspective.

00:11:12.575 --> 00:11:18.695
These are the miracles we can
physically see, and they represent

00:11:18.695 --> 00:11:22.034
only a small number of miracles.

00:11:22.034 --> 00:11:25.928
I would dare to say maybe 0.1%.

00:11:25.928 --> 00:11:27.597
Maybe even less.

00:11:27.597 --> 00:11:30.935
But what about the other miracles?

00:11:30.935 --> 00:11:38.725
You see, the other miracles are those
that will never come to public attention.

00:11:39.535 --> 00:11:44.529
For which we will never
know that they happened.

00:11:44.529 --> 00:11:47.858
These are the so-called inner miracles.

00:11:47.858 --> 00:11:53.408
It's the change of heart
that happens within a person.

00:11:53.408 --> 00:12:01.177
It's the peace that suddenly envelops
you, which you had no way of obtaining.

00:12:01.177 --> 00:12:08.946
It's the forgiveness you couldn't muster
your whole life, and suddenly you gave it.

00:12:08.946 --> 00:12:15.050
Everything that happens within a
person that we can't explain by

00:12:15.050 --> 00:12:18.935
anything else, that is also a miracle.

00:12:21.695 --> 00:12:28.893
And what I would like everyone to
remember is that a miracle is not proof.

00:12:28.893 --> 00:12:35.133
We might say, well, a miracle happened,
so that's proof that God exists.

00:12:35.133 --> 00:12:38.972
But that's not the purpose of a miracle.

00:12:38.972 --> 00:12:44.731
A miracle is not proof that
God exists, that God is here,

00:12:44.731 --> 00:12:48.091
but rather a miracle is a call.

00:12:48.091 --> 00:12:56.730
A call to me, a call to you, to come
back to the Lord and recognize Him again.

00:12:57.760 --> 00:13:06.239
This is how God speaks to us, saying,
"I am here, I am not far from you,

00:13:06.239 --> 00:13:12.723
believe." As we talk about miracles,
under the theme of Saint Anthony of

00:13:12.723 --> 00:13:18.708
Miracles, it would be remiss not to
say something about Saint Anthony.

00:13:18.708 --> 00:13:24.693
I don't have much time, so
I'll try to keep it brief.

00:13:24.693 --> 00:13:29.681
So, Saint Anthony, you've heard
of Saint Anthony, you regularly

00:13:29.681 --> 00:13:35.666
come here to our Basilica, you've
heard of him outside as well.

00:13:35.666 --> 00:13:43.647
He is actually a man whom people around
the world have decided to pray to and

00:13:43.647 --> 00:13:50.131
invoke for help when they lose keys,
documents, but also when they lose

00:13:50.131 --> 00:13:52.625
their identity, strength, or hope.

00:13:52.945 --> 00:13:55.903
Saint Anthony was born in Portugal.

00:13:55.903 --> 00:14:00.340
He was a Franciscan and
a very fervent preacher.

00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:08.230
But what is most important for us here
today and for this topic is that he

00:14:08.230 --> 00:14:15.625
left behind so much light that people
began to call him the Saint of Miracles.

00:14:15.625 --> 00:14:19.570
In other words, Saint
Anthony the Miracle Worker.

00:14:19.570 --> 00:14:23.515
As if he were the one performing miracles.

00:14:24.635 --> 00:14:29.808
But despite the fact that Saint
Anthony performed miracles during

00:14:29.808 --> 00:14:35.498
his lifetime, people didn't come
to him just because of that.

00:14:35.498 --> 00:14:42.224
They didn't say, "Oh, he performed
a miracle, let's go listen to him

00:14:42.224 --> 00:14:48.949
now." No, people came to him because
they felt God's presence through him.

00:14:48.949 --> 00:14:54.640
Because he exuded, he testified
and embodied God through his life.

00:14:55.359 --> 00:15:00.359
And yes, as he was like
that, miracles happened.

00:15:00.359 --> 00:15:06.468
But not because Saint Anthony
was some kind of superhero with

00:15:06.468 --> 00:15:10.912
superpowers or supernatural talents,
but because miracles happened

00:15:10.912 --> 00:15:15.356
through him since he was open to God.

00:15:15.356 --> 00:15:22.576
I won't list all the miracles, but
a few that happened during Saint

00:15:22.576 --> 00:15:26.465
Anthony's life, where he was the one...

00:15:27.155 --> 00:15:32.858
The first example where he was
the subject through whom a miracle

00:15:32.858 --> 00:15:38.086
occurred is when people didn't
want to listen to Saint Anthony.

00:15:38.086 --> 00:15:44.740
Saint Anthony stood at the edge of
the sea and began preaching to the

00:15:44.740 --> 00:15:50.919
fish, and the miracle that happened
was that the fish gathered, and you

00:15:50.919 --> 00:15:56.147
could see them listening to what Saint
Anthony was preaching, proclaiming,

00:15:56.147 --> 00:15:59.474
when people didn't want to do so.

00:15:59.555 --> 00:16:05.782
The second miracle occurred when
a mule knelt before the living

00:16:05.782 --> 00:16:08.613
Jesus in the Blessed Sacrament.

00:16:08.613 --> 00:16:18.238
A man did not want to believe, and to
prove it, he said that if this mule

00:16:18.238 --> 00:16:26.165
chose the Host, Jesus, over food, then
he would believe, because he did not

00:16:26.165 --> 00:16:29.562
believe that Jesus was present there.

00:16:29.562 --> 00:16:38.621
The man starved his mule, and after a
few days, when they came to St. Anthony,

00:16:38.621 --> 00:16:45.981
and St. Anthony raised the Blessed
Sacrament, food was placed to the side.

00:16:45.981 --> 00:16:54.474
The mule was hungry, and the first
thing it did was kneel and bow before

00:16:54.474 --> 00:16:57.305
Jesus in the Blessed Sacrament.

00:16:57.505 --> 00:16:59.319
And just a little digression.

00:16:59.319 --> 00:17:04.400
Often, as we stand up there during the
consecration, when we see that people

00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:09.481
do not kneel when the transformation
happens, when we lift up "this is my

00:17:09.481 --> 00:17:14.562
body, this is my blood," I wonder,
even that mule was less stubborn and

00:17:14.562 --> 00:17:17.103
had more faith than we sometimes do.

00:17:17.103 --> 00:17:22.910
So, can't I at least get down on my
knees for that minute and a half?

00:17:24.370 --> 00:17:29.614
Then Saint Anthony, wanting to
introduce some new laws and change

00:17:29.614 --> 00:17:34.859
the existing ones because they were
exploiting the people too much,

00:17:34.859 --> 00:17:42.010
was invited to a meal by a nobleman
who poisoned the food he was given.

00:17:42.010 --> 00:17:48.685
Saint Anthony prayed over the food and
ate it, and nothing happened to him.

00:17:48.685 --> 00:17:53.930
Even though the food was
poisoned and he should have died.

00:17:53.930 --> 00:17:56.303
And then that nobleman converted.

00:17:56.303 --> 00:18:00.099
Saint Anthony was in two places at once.

00:18:00.099 --> 00:18:05.795
There is an event where Saint
Anthony was preaching in a town.

00:18:05.795 --> 00:18:12.439
A great storm came, and the entire
town ended up underwater except for the

00:18:12.439 --> 00:18:15.287
square where Saint Anthony was preaching.

00:18:15.287 --> 00:18:20.982
We can say that in that circle,
that square, not a single

00:18:20.982 --> 00:18:23.830
drop of rain or water fell.

00:18:25.010 --> 00:18:30.571
He also brought a dead child back
to life, reattached a severed

00:18:30.571 --> 00:18:35.669
leg to a young man—literally,
the leg was three meters away.

00:18:35.669 --> 00:18:42.620
He took the leg and, like connecting Lego
pieces, reattached it to the young man.

00:18:42.620 --> 00:18:48.182
This was considered a miracle at
the time when Saint Anthony lived.

00:18:48.182 --> 00:18:54.206
Even today, such a reattachment is
not possible as Saint Anthony did it.

00:18:54.206 --> 00:19:00.231
He also resurrected a dead man who
had been murdered, and Saint Anthony's

00:19:00.231 --> 00:19:03.012
father was accused of the murder.

00:19:03.012 --> 00:19:09.964
Saint Anthony went to the grave where
the man was buried and told the dead

00:19:09.964 --> 00:19:14.135
man to rise and say who had killed him.

00:19:14.794 --> 00:19:19.215
The dead man rose from the grave,
named his killer, and returned back.

00:19:21.915 --> 00:19:27.825
Maybe it sounds funny, maybe like
something out of a movie, but that's

00:19:27.825 --> 00:19:33.280
how it happened and that's how
it's recorded, and we believe it.

00:19:33.280 --> 00:19:35.099
And that's a miracle.

00:19:35.099 --> 00:19:40.554
Because we can't prove a miracle,
we can only believe in it.

00:19:40.554 --> 00:19:46.919
But listening to all this, Saint Anthony
was not a magician, someone who would

00:19:46.919 --> 00:19:52.830
just perform a trick; rather, Saint
Anthony was always a guide towards Jesus.

00:19:53.550 --> 00:20:01.591
And Saint Anthony never said, after
any miracle, look at me, I did this.

00:20:01.591 --> 00:20:07.909
Instead, he always said, look
at Jesus, don't look at me.

00:20:07.909 --> 00:20:14.227
And that was actually the miraculous
power that Saint Anthony had.

00:20:14.227 --> 00:20:17.099
He showed God, not himself.

00:20:17.099 --> 00:20:22.843
And that was during the time
of Saint Anthony, centuries

00:20:22.843 --> 00:20:26.289
ago, but what about us today?

00:20:26.289 --> 00:20:29.736
What about in our present time?

00:20:29.736 --> 00:20:36.628
We often hear and often repeat
the phrase, there are no more

00:20:36.628 --> 00:20:40.075
miracles like there used to be.

00:20:40.075 --> 00:20:43.171
So why aren't there any?

00:20:43.171 --> 00:20:46.268
And that might be true.

00:20:46.268 --> 00:20:53.700
But again, maybe it's not about
the miracles, but about our eyes.

00:20:53.700 --> 00:21:02.370
Because God has never stopped working,
not at any point in history, nor now.

00:21:02.370 --> 00:21:06.705
Maybe we've just forgotten how to see.

00:21:06.705 --> 00:21:12.899
Because today, we always look for
some sensation, something spectacular.

00:21:12.899 --> 00:21:16.615
But God often gives us presence.

00:21:18.535 --> 00:21:19.996
We look for some sign.

00:21:19.996 --> 00:21:24.967
"God, give me a sign for this, God,
give me a sign for that, so I know

00:21:24.967 --> 00:21:29.353
where I'll be tomorrow, where I'll be
the day after, what I'll eat, what I'll

00:21:29.353 --> 00:21:33.739
drink. Will I wake up, give me some
sign." But God often doesn't give us

00:21:33.739 --> 00:21:35.786
signs; instead, He gives us a person.

00:21:35.786 --> 00:21:39.587
First, Himself in the person of Jesus
Christ, then others who are entrusted

00:21:39.587 --> 00:21:43.973
to us, who will then tell us something,
convey a message, and through that, we

00:21:43.973 --> 00:21:46.020
will recognize what God is giving us.

00:21:46.420 --> 00:21:52.089
So it doesn't have to be a sign
that it's a miracle, but rather the

00:21:52.089 --> 00:21:54.735
person God has placed in your life.

00:21:54.735 --> 00:22:00.027
Similarly, I often look for that click,
for something to happen in an instant,

00:22:00.027 --> 00:22:02.295
and that's it, that's the miracle.

00:22:02.295 --> 00:22:05.319
But God often doesn't
give us such miracles.

00:22:05.319 --> 00:22:08.343
Instead, God often calls us on a journey.

00:22:08.343 --> 00:22:13.257
Then, on that journey, over a certain
period of time—maybe throughout our whole

00:22:13.257 --> 00:22:19.305
life, maybe a week, maybe a day—He allows
us to reach the miracle we are seeking.

00:22:19.505 --> 00:22:23.517
But to stay on the path with Him.

00:22:23.517 --> 00:22:30.538
Because a miracle can be forgiveness that
you never thought you would give, and

00:22:30.538 --> 00:22:33.046
sometimes that forgiveness takes time.

00:22:33.046 --> 00:22:39.566
A sense of peace amidst the
chaos of life in which I live.

00:22:39.566 --> 00:22:44.079
Maybe spiritual strength when
I'm completely down and don't

00:22:44.079 --> 00:22:47.089
think I'll ever get up again.

00:22:47.089 --> 00:22:53.609
I believe that each of you, at
least once in your life, has

00:22:53.609 --> 00:22:59.125
experienced a miracle, but perhaps
you didn't recognize it because it

00:22:59.125 --> 00:23:02.135
didn't look like a "movie miracle."

00:23:04.615 --> 00:23:11.032
But when we talk about miracles like
this, the question always arises:

00:23:11.032 --> 00:23:15.311
today, here, now, do I need a miracle?

00:23:15.311 --> 00:23:19.590
Do I need a miracle in my life?

00:23:22.800 --> 00:23:25.250
What miracle do you need?

00:23:25.250 --> 00:23:31.620
What is inside you and in your
heart that you wish would change,

00:23:31.620 --> 00:23:35.050
something you can't do on your own?

00:23:35.050 --> 00:23:37.990
In you or in someone else?

00:23:37.990 --> 00:23:42.889
Not something that would be
"nice to have." Not that.

00:23:42.889 --> 00:23:47.790
But something without which you
feel like you're falling apart,

00:23:47.790 --> 00:23:53.179
without which you can't go on,
without which you're breaking down.

00:23:53.179 --> 00:23:58.570
What is that miracle that
you need in your life today?

00:23:58.830 --> 00:24:04.744
Maybe you want to stop feeling
invisible because no one notices you.

00:24:04.744 --> 00:24:10.659
Maybe you want to stop pretending
that everything is okay in your

00:24:10.659 --> 00:24:13.617
life when you know it's not.

00:24:13.617 --> 00:24:17.560
Maybe you want to feel
loved, accepted, free.

00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:22.982
You see, when we recognize
these things and pray for them,

00:24:22.982 --> 00:24:25.940
that's a prayer for a miracle.

00:24:25.940 --> 00:24:28.404
But there's just one problem.

00:24:28.404 --> 00:24:31.855
And the problem is in the box.

00:24:32.955 --> 00:24:35.031
Nothing without this box today.

00:24:35.031 --> 00:24:36.692
I need a volunteer.

00:24:36.692 --> 00:24:41.675
I mean, I need two hands, one
to hold the microphone, so...

00:24:44.370 --> 00:24:51.744
It's not complicated at all, just
stand there, look nice, and hold this.

00:24:51.744 --> 00:24:53.445
See this jar?

00:24:53.445 --> 00:25:00.819
You can lift it a bit so
those in the back can see.

00:25:00.819 --> 00:25:04.223
This jar represents us, our shell.

00:25:04.223 --> 00:25:11.030
Each of us, at our baptism,
truly becomes a Child of God.

00:25:12.605 --> 00:25:16.613
At our baptism, we received the Holy
Spirit, God settled within us, and this

00:25:16.613 --> 00:25:18.617
candle that will be lit represents that.

00:25:18.617 --> 00:25:22.625
You can just lower it, you don't have
to lower yourself, just your hands.

00:25:26.235 --> 00:25:34.282
And this candle now speaks within us,
it burns and speaks, but it also speaks.

00:25:34.282 --> 00:25:39.111
This candle shines just
as God shines within us.

00:25:39.111 --> 00:25:43.403
So where does the problem
with miracles occur?

00:25:43.403 --> 00:25:48.768
You see, this candle burns
because the jar is open.

00:25:48.768 --> 00:25:57.352
What happens in our lives is that we
often close ourselves off, just as we are.

00:25:57.352 --> 00:26:01.645
I love you, hold it a bit tighter.

00:26:04.295 --> 00:26:05.235
Thank you.

00:26:05.235 --> 00:26:08.529
Alright, we need to open it later.

00:26:08.529 --> 00:26:11.352
Thank you, you can sit down.

00:26:11.352 --> 00:26:16.527
You see, this candle, even though
it's closed, no longer burns.

00:26:16.527 --> 00:26:18.409
It burned a little.

00:26:18.409 --> 00:26:23.114
It burned as long as
there was oxygen in it.

00:26:23.114 --> 00:26:27.349
Because oxygen is needed
for the flame to survive.

00:26:27.349 --> 00:26:29.701
And this happens within us.

00:26:29.701 --> 00:26:35.818
We close ourselves off and then
expect that the little bit left in

00:26:35.818 --> 00:26:42.405
us, the bit of God that remains, once
it burns out, there's nothing left.

00:26:42.405 --> 00:26:46.512
We expect miracles to continue
happening in our lives.

00:26:46.512 --> 00:26:51.075
And we pray for miracles
to happen in others' lives.

00:26:51.075 --> 00:26:55.639
But how can they happen when
the connection is broken?

00:26:55.639 --> 00:26:57.465
You see, you see

00:27:07.280 --> 00:27:15.652
You see, this candle that represents
God in our lives, as I said,

00:27:15.652 --> 00:27:24.669
it can only burn if the glass
is open, just like we are open.

00:27:24.669 --> 00:27:29.821
And it will burn, it won't burn anymore.

00:27:29.821 --> 00:27:31.753
I'm not lucky.

00:27:31.753 --> 00:27:35.617
But maybe a miracle will happen.

00:27:35.617 --> 00:27:44.634
It will burn as long as we
don't cast God out of our lives.

00:27:44.634 --> 00:27:47.854
And that's important to know.

00:27:47.854 --> 00:27:51.075
And that's what God does.

00:27:51.355 --> 00:27:58.192
Maybe God, when we are open to Him,
won't give us the miracle we ask for,

00:27:58.192 --> 00:28:04.174
"My God, do it exactly this way."
Instead, God will give us what we

00:28:04.174 --> 00:28:07.165
need, not just what we often want.

00:28:07.165 --> 00:28:14.003
Because we must be aware that God is
not a machine where we insert a token

00:28:14.003 --> 00:28:16.994
and get exactly what we dialed in.

00:28:16.994 --> 00:28:21.695
No, God is our Father who
is always there with us.

00:28:24.540 --> 00:28:29.584
And finally, to wrap things up,
I've gone a bit overboard—it'll be a

00:28:29.584 --> 00:28:34.240
miracle if Stjepan doesn't strangle
me, but they say miracles do happen.

00:28:34.560 --> 00:28:39.484
But here's perhaps one more
question for the end that might

00:28:39.484 --> 00:28:41.723
not have crossed your mind.

00:28:41.723 --> 00:28:47.096
The question is this, a rhetorical
statement if I may say so.

00:28:47.096 --> 00:28:50.677
Maybe you're not here
to receive a miracle.

00:28:50.677 --> 00:28:56.050
Maybe you're here to be a miracle,
because Saint Anthony was just

00:28:56.050 --> 00:28:59.184
a man like we are just people.

00:28:59.184 --> 00:29:05.900
But you too can be, just like Saint
Anthony was, an answer to a prayer.

00:29:07.160 --> 00:29:12.477
Your smile, your listening, your
message, and your presence, maybe that's

00:29:12.477 --> 00:29:19.244
actually a miracle for someone who
will find a way out of the darkness.

00:29:19.244 --> 00:29:26.011
Because you don't have to be that
saint on the icon in the picture.

00:29:26.011 --> 00:29:26.495
No.

00:29:26.495 --> 00:29:35.196
You need to be the one who dares to
say, "God, here I am, use me." And maybe

00:29:35.196 --> 00:29:41.480
the miracle you need is the miracle
you will become for someone else.

00:29:42.985 --> 00:29:44.968
So, I'll finish with this.

00:29:44.968 --> 00:29:47.745
Thank you very much for your attention.

